    "These dimensions include task formulation, dataset composition, and fine-tuning methods.",
    "Table 3 provides a structured overview of key design choices and their rationales.",
    "The following discussion details each of these dimensions, examining implementation patterns and empirical findings reported in the literature.The formulation of fine-tuning tasks exhibits significant diversity.",
    "The most prevalent form is code-to-test generation, where the input typically comprises the source code of the focal method and its class context, while the output is a complete unit test case [5,126].",
    "To address the core test oracle problem, other studies focus on assertion generation, structuring the input as the focal method and an existing test prefix, with the model output restricted to the missing assertion statements [124].Early systematic research has also validated the effectiveness of fine-tuning models such as CodeT5 for assertion generation, revealing that the generated assertions can detect more real-world defects than traditional methods [168]."
